-- Asics Cuts Full-Year Profit Forecast 13% to $124 Million on Yen's Strength
-- B y   A d a m   L e
-- 2010-11-04T06:12:37Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-04/asics-cuts-full-year-profit-forecast-13-to-124-million-on-yen-s-strength.html
Asics Corp., the Japanese sporting
goods and shoe maker, cut its annual profit forecast 13 percent.  Net income will probably total 10 billion yen ($124
million) in the year ending March 2011, compared with the
previous projection of 11.5 billion yen, the Kobe-based company
said in a statement today.  Profit more than doubled to 5.51 billion yen in the six
months ended Sept. 30, the company said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
